The electric dipole moment is given by \( p = qd \), where \( q = 1.50 \, \text{nC} = 1.50 \times 10^{-9} \, \text{C} \) and \( d = 6.20 \, \mu\text{m} = 6.20 \times 10^{-6} \, \text{m} \).  
Multiplying gives \( p = (1.50 \times 10^{-9})(6.20 \times 10^{-6}) = 9.30 \times 10^{-15} \, \text{C} \cdot \text{m} \).  

